                                        2118,
                                        2806
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "Capital Structure: Long (or short) credit and short (or long) equity. A typical example is buying a bond (long credit) and buying an equity put option (short credit). Such positions are usually delta- neutral and gamma- long. Senior Sub: Long senior credit and short subordinated credit. A typical example is buying a senior bond and buying subordinated CDS protection against it. Such positions are usually theta- negative and delta- short (meaning they profit from credit widening)."
                                }
